  "texts": [
    "A vast majority of errors occur at the prescribing stage, accounting for 70% of errors that result in adverse patient events.",
    "5 Halting errors at this stage is critical in preventing perpetuation of the error downstream and eventually reaching the patient.",
    "Clinical Decision Support Systems (CDSS) have become a cornerstone of modern healthcare systems as a direct aid to clinical decision making.",
    "A CDSS is intended to improve healthcare delivery by enhancing medical decisions with targeted clinical knowledge, patient information, and other health information.",
    "6 A key function of CDSS is in reducing the incidence of prescribing or medication errors and adverse events through integration with electronic health records and computerized provider order entry (CPOE) systems."
  ],
